(1000, 'A + B Problem', '<div class="ctitle">\r\nDescription\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\nA + B Problem\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Input</div>\r\n<p>\r\nTwo integers.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Output</div>\r\n<p>\r\nOne line, the answer.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Sample Input</div>\r\n<pre>\r\n3 5\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Sample Output</div>\r\n<pre>\r\n8\r\n</pre>', 1000, 131072, 0, 0, 1, 1, 0, 1),
(1001, 'Cirno''s Perfect Math Class', '<div class="ctitle">\r\nDescription\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\nCirno''s perfect math class is fashionable over the world. But now, sadly, it must be stopped for some reason. In the last class, N students attended, and each student gave a gift to Cirno. But the gifts are too many so that Cirno just want to take K(K is non-negative) gifts away. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAs we all know, Cirno loves the number ⑨. Assume there are P ways to take away K gifts. If P > 0 and P is a multiple of 9, Cirno will accept K as a alternative plan. Now, Cirno want to know how many plans that she has to think over.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Input</div>\r\n<p>\r\nThe number of test cases T(integer, about 50) will be given in the first line.\r\nThen T lines follow. and each line contains a non-negative integer N(N &lt;= 10^1000).\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Output</div>\r\n<p>\r\nOne line for each case, the answer.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Sample Input</div>\r\n<pre>\r\n3\r\n5\r\n9\r\n10\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Sample Output</div>\r\n<pre>\r\n0\r\n6\r\n3\r\n</pre>', 1000, 131072, 0, 0, 1, 1, 0, 0),
(1002, 'Magic', '<div class="ctitle">\r\nDescription\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\nPuella Magi Magick loves eating cheeses. And her brother has so many cheeses but he won''t give her more then <var>M</var> cheeses. Magick is unhappy, because she really wants more more more more more cheeses! At last, brother allowed that she can use <strong>MAGIC</strong> to double her cheeses only when she finds a number <var>S</var> which is not more than <var>T</var> and the greatest common divisor of <var>S</var> and <var>T</var> is 1, where <var>T</var> is the amount of cheeses she took away from him. Note that a required number can be used only once.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nAs a Puella Magi, Magick is so clever that she can find all required numbers, so she can double or redouble her cheeses again and again! But Magick don''t know how many cheeses she can eat at most. Can you help little Magick? &gt;_&lt;\r\n</p>\r\n<div class="ctitle">Input</div>\r\n<p>\r\nThe number of test cases <var>T</var>(integer, about 500) will be given in the first line.\r\nThen <var>T</var> lines follow. and each line contains a non-negative integer <var>M</var>(<var>M</var> &lt;= 2<sup>54</sup>).\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Output</div>\r\n<p>\r\nOne line for each case, the answer module 1000000007.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Sample Input</div>\r\n<pre>\r\n3\r\n4\r\n5\r\n6\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<div class="ctitle">Sample Output</div>\r\n<pre>\r\n16\r\n80\r\n80\r\n</pre>\r\n<div class="ctitle">Hint</div>\r\n<p>\r\nExample:\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n1. Brother can give Magick 4 cheeses, and Magick took all away and found the numbers 1 and 3. So Magick could double cheeses twice, and got 4 * 2 * 2 = 16 cheeses at last.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n2. Brother can give Magick 5 cheeses, and Magick took all away and found the numbers 1, 2, 3 and 4. So Magick could double cheeses four times, and got 5 * 2 * 2 * 2 * 2 = 80 cheeses at last.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n3. Brother can give Magick 6 cheeses. If Magick had took all away and she would only find the numbers 1 and 5, so Magick could double cheeses twice, and just got 6 * 2 * 2 = 24 cheeses at last. But Magick just took 5 of them and found the numbers 1, 2, 3 and 4, so that she would get 5 * 2 * 2 * 2 * 2 = 80 cheeses at last.\r\n</p>\r\n', 1000, 131072, 0, 0, 1, 1, 0, 0);
